<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-03T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119P43/844: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-03T14:00:00-05:00">December 3, 1919—2
                            p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                    <p>3948. Confidential for Polk. Your No. 5531 of December 2, 6 p.m. The
                        President has stated that his decision which was communicated to you in my
                        telegram No. 3941 of December 2, 4 p.m. was to be regarded as final.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>